-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Dubai Investments, Dubai Islamic Bank
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-03-21T10:46:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/persian-gulf-stocks-dubai-investments-commercial-bank-of-qatar.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.7
percent, the biggest increase since March 13, to 1,655.50 at the
2 p.m. close in Dubai.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained 0.3
percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Dubai Investments PJSC (DIC)   advanced the most in more
than a week, surging 5.1 percent to 92 fils. The owner of stakes
in more than 40 companies said its board recommended a cash
dividend of 5 fils a share for last year.  Dubai Islamic Bank PJSC (DIB)   gained for the second time
this week, rising 1.4 percent to 2.22 dirhams. The United Arab
Emirates’ biggest bank complying with Shariah rules raised the
dividend payment for last year to 12.5 fils a share after
cutting it earlier to comply with central bank’s directions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
